Reasoning: The paper deals with the problem of oriented coloring on directed graphs, which is a topic in graph theory. The use of co-graphs and recursively defined digraphs suggests a connection to discrete mathematics (cs.DM) and data structures (cs.DS). The study of chromatic numbers and graph isomorphism also falls under computational geometry (cs.CG) and graph theory (cs.GT). Finally, the complexity analysis of the algorithms used in the paper relates to computational complexity (cs.CC).
